         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Framework agreement for the purchase of environmental engineering and geological consultancy services.</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>18/00283</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="14000000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>DMF wants to enter into parallel framework agreements with two or more tenderers in a cross-discipline assignment spectrum. The agreement primarily comprises projects connected to pollution (&gt;70 % of the assignments). The contribution can comprise professional assessment in environmental geology / engineering, biology, planning discipline, geological engineering, mining engineering and administrative services such as project and construction management.</P>
               <P>The agreement may also comprise assistance in connection with securing of abandoned mines and for processing of operative licenses, i.e. assignments requiring rock engineering/geological competence, geoengineering, planning and natural environment assessments.</P>
               <P>The assignments under the framework agreement will be of different natures and can consist of general consultancy services through meetings, preparation of minutes and documents in addition to larger reports and risk assessments.</P>
               <P>The assignments may also be connected to site inspections, supervision, meetings with other authorities and information and communications activities.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
